ce:section.ce:para:
The melanin@N-GQDs@MIP sensing probe was applied to determine prometryn in vegetable samples (Table 1
                        ). Satisfactory recoveries of 94.2–101.0 % were obtained from the spiked radish sprout samples, 96.2–101.7 % were achieved from tomato samples, 97.6–101.2 % were achieved from the basil paste samples and 97.1–101.3 % were achieved for the olive brine samples. The RSDs of less than 6 % indicated good precision. The results suggested that the melanin@N-GQDs@MIP nano-fluorescence probe provided promising application for the actual analysis of prometryn in real food samples. The analytical results of spiked samples also agree well with the HPLC method (Fig. 6
                        ).
